Traimo nepoznate podatke

imaNedostajucih = 0;
for (col_name in names(mutual_funds)){
  if (sum(is.na(mutual_funds[,col_name])) > 0){
    cat('Ukupno nedostajuih vrijednosti za varijablu ',col_name, ': ', sum(is.na(mutual_funds[,col_name])),'\n')
    imaNedostajucih = 1;
  } 
}
## Ukupno nedostajucih vrijednosti za varijablu  net_assets :  2
if(!imaNedostajucih) {
  cat("Nema nedostajucih podataka")
}

POdjela na grupu s outlierima i bez outliera

mutual_funds_outliers <- mutual_funds
Q <- quantile(mutual_funds$success, probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm = FALSE)
iqr <- IQR(mutual_funds$success)
mutual_funds <- subset(mutual_funds, mutual_funds$success > (Q[1] - 1.5*iqr) & mutual_funds$success < (Q[2]+1.5*iqr))
hist(mutual_funds$net_annual_expense_ratio_fund,main='Net annual expense ratio fund[%]', xlab='Expense ratio', ylab='Frequency')

Budui da imamo veliku koliinu podataka, moemo pretpostaviti normalnost.

Provjeravamo normalnost

library(nortest)
## Warning: package 'nortest' was built under R version 4.0.3
lillie.test(mutual_funds$success)
## 
##  Lilliefors (Kolmogorov-Smirnov) normality test
## 
## data:  mutual_funds$success
## D = 0.021208, p-value = 1.536e-06
lillie.test(mutual_funds_outliers$success)
## 
##  Lilliefors (Kolmogorov-Smirnov) normality test
## 
## data:  mutual_funds_outliers$success
## D = 0.087033, p-value < 2.2e-16

Ovo ne valja

Provjeravamo varijanice

var(mutual_funds_expensive$success)
## [1] 2.405038
var(mutual_funds_cheap$success)
## [1] 1.940572

Usporeujemo jednakost varijanci

var.test(mutual_funds_expensive$success, mutual_funds_cheap$success)
## 
##  F test to compare two variances
## 
## data:  mutual_funds_expensive$success and mutual_funds_cheap$success
## F = 1.2393, num df = 2768, denom df = 3327, p-value = 3.373e-09
## alternative hypothesis: true ratio of variances is not equal to 1
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  1.154168 1.331123
## sample estimates:
## ratio of variances 
##           1.239345

Odbijamo pretpostavku H_0 da su varijance jednake. Koristimo t-test

t.test(mutual_funds_cheap$success, mutual_funds_expensive$success, alt = "greater", var.equal = FALSE)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  mutual_funds_cheap$success and mutual_funds_expensive$success
## t = 21.412, df = 5623.5, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is greater than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.7531311       Inf
## sample estimates:
##  mean of x  mean of y 
##  0.3095493 -0.5062622

MOemo rei da su jeftiniji fondovi u prosjeku uspjeniji.

Gledamo neparametarski Mann-Whitney-Wilcoxov test

wilcox.test(mutual_funds_cheap$success, mutual_funds_expensive$success, alternative = "greater")
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  mutual_funds_cheap$success and mutual_funds_expensive$success
## W = 6101732, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is greater than 0
wilcox.test(mutual_funds_outliers_cheap$success, mutual_funds_outliers_expensive$success, alternative = "greater")

prop.test(rating_proportions,rating_sum, alt="greater")
## 
##  2-sample test for equality of proportions with continuity correction
## 
## data:  rating_proportions out of rating_sum

## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.1762917 1.0000000
## sample estimates:
##    prop 1    prop 2

Odbacujemo hipotezu H_0 da su proporcije visoko rangiranih fondova jednake kod skupljih i jeftinijih fondova. Moemo zakljuiti da jeftiniji fondovi imaju veu proporciju visoko rangiranih fondova.
